cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DL, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the formalization and axiomatization of mathematical theories, which is a topic closely related to logic. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the organization and maintenance of a library of formalized mathematics, which can be seen as a software engineering problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with the development of different axiomatizations of a theory, which can be seen as different programming languages for expressing the same concepts. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper discusses the organization and management of a library of formalized mathematics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the development of a structure for consolidating knowledge, which can be seen as a knowledge representation problem in AI.
